parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Filler Neck Solder Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank filler neck solder joint can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and others on the road.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline
fuel leaks from the filler neck
fuel spills on the ground
fuel fumes emanating from the vehicle
rattling noise from the fuel tank
and loose baffles in the tank.

and loose baffles in the tank.
